      "span_text": "The diagnostic strategy underlying the use of ventilation-perfusion scintigraphy in the workup for pulmonary embolism is based on Bayesian analysis  , which postulates that for a reasonably sensitive and specific test, the lower the pretest probability, the more likely it is that a positive test result will be false, and the higher the pretest probability, the more likely it is that a negative test result will be false."
